Sri Lanka has held its first mass funeral amid a day of mourning for the victims of Sunday’s bomb blasts. The death toll from the attacks on churches and hotels has risen to 321 with about 500 wounded, police said. A state of emergency is in effect to prevent further attacks. The Islamic State (IS) group claimed the attack on Tuesday via its news outlet. Sri Lanka’s government has blamed the blasts on local Islamist group National Thowheed Jamath (NTJ). Sri Lanka bombings: Over 30 foreigners among 207 persons killed Sri Lanka attack: Death toll rises to 290 Sri Lanka: Bombings: Govt failed to act on intelligence